turnkey-appengine-python-12.0 (1) turnkey; urgency=low

  * Initial public release of TurnKey Linux AppEngine Python.

  * Google App Engine configurations

    - Preconfigured cgi, webapp and django appengine application templates

        - /var/www/appengine/template-*

    - Template-Django is preconfigured for NoSQL:

        - http://www.allbuttonspressed.com/projects/djangoappengine

    - Includes welcome page with useful information and link to offline
      documentation.

  * Includes TurnKey Web Control panel with useful information, references,
    and link to offline documentation (convenience).

  * Regenerates all secrets during installation / firstboot (security).

  * Includes python imaging library (PIL) for appengine Image API.

  * Major component versions

    google_appengine            1.6.5
    google-appengine-docs       20120228
    template-django             pulled from upstream repo: 2012-05-03
    antlr_python_runtime        3.1.3

    lighttpd                    1.4.28-2+squeeze1
    postfix                     2.7.1-1+squeeze1
    python-imaging              1.1.7-2

  * Note: Please refer to turnkey-core's changelog for changes common to all
    appliances. Here we only describe changes specific to this appliance.

 -- Alon Swartz <alon@turnkeylinux.org>  Wed, 01 Aug 2012 08:00:00 +0200

